I say this oversight is neoterici ,· since the true position of the Boii was nearer Bohemia than the text of note in o. Boiohemwm makes it. Still, the correction by no means carries it as far east as Bohemia; since the plain meaning of ulteriore is not aoy part east of the Maine, but the parts that immediately (there or thereabouts) succeed, or come next to, the Helvetiae occupancy. Now, these are parts (and no inconsiderable parts either) of Bavaria. Bohe- mia, undoubtedly, comes afterwards in the same direction; but so do Gallicia and many other places.
